@startuml approach1-linq-detailed-activity
title **Approach 1: InMemoryContainer — LINQ Query Flow (Detailed)**

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #333
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam PartitionBorderColor #666

|Test Setup|
start
:**InMemoryFeedIteratorSetup.Register()**
→ sets **AsyncLocal<FeedIteratorFactory>**
= **CreateInMemoryFeedIterator<T>**
(one-time, per test fixture);

note right
  Resolution order in ToFeedIteratorOverridable:
  1. AsyncLocal factory (per-async-flow) ← matches in tests
  2. StaticFallbackFactory (static field)
  3. Real SDK .ToFeedIterator() (production path)
end note

|InMemoryContainer|
:Call **GetItemLinqQueryable<T>**
(allowSynchronousQueryExecution,
continuationToken, requestOptions);

:**GetAllItemsForPartition**(requestOptions)
→ read from ConcurrentDictionary store
→ filter by partition key if specified
→ exclude TTL-expired items
→ return List<string> (JSON);

:Deserialize each JSON string →
**JsonConvert.DeserializeObject<T>()**;

:Apply requestOptions.PartitionKey
filtering if specified;

:items.**AsQueryable()**
.**OrderBy**(item => 0)
→ **IOrderedQueryable<T>**;

note right
  This is a plain **LINQ-to-Objects** queryable —
  NOT the Cosmos SDK's CosmosLinqQueryProvider.
  All operators execute as C# delegates, not SQL.
  No SQL parsing involved in this flow.
end note

:Return IOrderedQueryable<T> to caller;

|Test Code|
:Apply LINQ operators (no execution yet):
.**Where**(x => x.Status == "active")
→ adds predicate delegate
.**Select**(x => x.Name)
→ adds projection delegate
.**OrderBy**(x => x.Timestamp)
→ adds sort key delegate
.**Take**(10)
→ adds limit;

note right
  These are standard System.Linq
  operators on IQueryable<T>.
  They compose a deferred pipeline —
  no items are evaluated yet.
end note

|ProductionExtensions|
:Call .**ToFeedIteratorOverridable**()
(CosmosOverridableFeedIteratorExtensions);

:Check **AsyncLocal<FeedIteratorFactory>**
→ non-null (set by Register());

|InMemoryFeedIteratorSetup|
:factory.Invoke(queryable) =
**CreateInMemoryFeedIterator<T>**(queryable);

:queryable.**AsEnumerable**()
→ **triggers LINQ-to-Objects execution**:
Where delegate → Select delegate →
OrderBy delegate → Take delegate
all run as C# delegates in-memory;

:Create **new InMemoryFeedIterator<T>**
(materialized IEnumerable<T>,
maxItemCount from requestOptions);

:Return FeedIterator<T>;

|Test Code|
while (FeedIter.HasMoreResults?) is (yes)
  :Call **ReadNextAsync()**;

  |InMemoryFeedIterator<T>|
  :**EnsureItems**()
  → materialize enumerable on first call
  → cache results for subsequent pages;

  :Paginate: **Skip**(offset).**Take**(maxItemCount)
  → extract current page;

  :Generate **continuation token**
  → offset-based integer
  → null if last page;

  :Create **new InMemoryFeedResponse<T>**
  (page of items, continuationToken,
  Headers: x-ms-request-charge,
  x-ms-activity-id);

  |Test Code|
  :Receive **FeedResponse<T>**;

endwhile (no)

stop

@enduml
